118
00:18:31,819 --> 00:18:41,849
Software metrics aim to transfer the way we reason about software systems.

119
00:18:41,849 --> 00:18:47,039
Instead of depending on or relying on intuition or information.

120
00:18:47,039 --> 00:18:49,039
Or informal judgments.

121
00:18:49,039 --> 00:18:58,640
Measurement provides a structured way to describe and analyze software attributes.

122
00:18:58,640 --> 00:19:05,640
In many engineering disciplines physical instruments such as thermometers or rulers.

123
00:19:05,640 --> 00:19:11,799
Are used to map real world properties into numbers.

124
00:19:11,799 --> 00:19:18,279
Software measurements face a similar challenge.

125
00:19:18,279 --> 00:19:23,440
But it usually operates without physical artifacts.

126
00:19:23,440 --> 00:19:32,470
To measure software effectively it is not enough to simply collect numbers.

127
00:19:32,470 --> 00:19:48,240
We must first understand how our observations are connected to numerical representations.

128
00:19:48,240 --> 00:19:55,200
And why these representations are valid.

129
00:19:55,200 --> 00:20:08,940
This means we need to move beyond intuition and base measurement on representational theory.

130
00:20:08,940 --> 00:20:18,940
Representational theory explains how properties of the real world can be translated into numerical systems.

131
00:20:18,940 --> 00:20:24,000
While preserving meaningful relationships.

132
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:31,769
Only when this historical bridge is clearly defined.

133
